	(298,3,'2014-07-10 11:24:52','2014-07-10 08:24:52','<p>I have volunteered with RAHU since 2011 and I have seen it grow as evidenced through the different events, activities and set strategies in RAHU, I can truly say; I have had an amazing experience working with it and it has partly made me who I am today.</p><p>Through RAHUs Peer Educators Academy that kicked off earlier in January 2014, I got to learn a lot from the different mentors who set the youth development strategies high hence benefiting much more to what was expected.</p><p>RAHUs out reaches have also been a great deal to me and actually an amazing experience because they have groomed me into someone who can speak out to a large crowd with full confidence, which was not the case in the days before I joined RAHU, on that note I credit RAHU for that.</p><p>And then came the camp, being among those who tasted RAHUs first sleep away camp in a period of six nights and five days introductory and learning sessions, I can gladly say everything came out successful through a lot of involvement and participation amongst campers, partners and the inspirational speakers who were part of the main drivers of the camp.</p><p>It was such another new amazing experience and therefore congratulate RAHU upon that and also on how far it has reached.</p>','Never Been The Same: Juliana Namata','','publish','open','open','','never-been-the-same-juliana-namata','','','2017-07-05 18:51:06','2017-07-05 15:51:06','',0,'http://localhost/rahu/?p=298',0,'post','',0),
