	(331,3,'2014-11-23 12:33:29','2014-11-23 09:33:29','<p>As lead up to the World AIDs Day celebration, we at Reach A Hand with support from our partners atKyuka Youth Outreach, a community based youth organization that uses dance and creative arts to transform and empower young people. We hosted a Flash Mob Activations in Kisenyi a Kampala sub with the citys centrally located slums. Also a place with many languages spoken in Uganda including nations from Eastern Congo, Tanzania, Rwanda, Kenya, Somalia and Ethiopia, Kisenyi youth lack access to reliable and comprehensive sexual and reproductive health and rights (SRHR) information and the corresponding life skills.</p><p>A mobile HIV Testing and Counseling hub was set up at Muzana Zone (lorry/taxi Park) and over 21,000 condoms supplied by UNFPA and UHMG were distributed to young people</p>','RAHU Hosts Flash Mob Activations In Kisenyi','','publish','open','open','','rahu-hosts-flash-mob-activations-in-kisenyi','','','2017-07-06 18:28:30','2017-07-06 15:28:30','',0,'http://localhost/rahu/?p=331',0,'post','',0),
